duties_responsibilities.duty: Oversee clinical services and initiatives for women, men, children, and adolescents
Ensure coordination of services with Medicaid and community-based providers
Assure compliance with State and Federal laws, regulations, and guidelines
Provide specialized interpretation of policies and procedures
Negotiate and implement contracts for underserved areas and specialty services
Develop and submit funding applications and progress reports
Supervise program staff and oversee their duties

education_certification.credential: Baccalaureate degree plus five years of professional level experience in administrative services, economics, public health, public relations, social services, health services, or surveying and/or assessing health or social service programs or facilities for compliance with state and federal regulations.
